From: expo-pico maintainers
Subject: [PATCH] OpenXR: log XrResult on failure + survive when XR_KHR_android_create_instance is unavailable

Two changes to virocore's OpenXR backend that together unblock PICO OS 6:

  1. The XR_RETURN_FALSE / XR_RETURN_NULL macros around xrCreateInstance
     today discard the actual XrResult. On PICO the loader-level log just
     says "LoaderInstance::CreateInstance chained CreateInstance call failed"
     and Viro logs "result=-1" — neither tells us which XrResult enum the
     runtime returned. Without that diagnostic, every PICO regression looks
     identical. This patch routes the real result through ALOGE before the
     macro returns.

  2. XR_KHR_android_create_instance is listed as REQUIRED today. PICO's
     OpenXR runtime supports the extension on OS 6 but a) some PICO 4
     firmware revisions enumerate it as a runtime extension (queryable
     via xrEnumerateInstanceExtensionProperties) rather than as a loader
     extension, and b) on the strict PICO Swan runtime the loader rejects
     the createInstance call entirely if the host App didn't pre-prime
     XR_KHR_loader_init_android with valid Java VM + Activity references.
     This patch:
       - enumerates the available extensions BEFORE building the required-
         list, so we can downgrade XR_KHR_android_create_instance from
         "required" to "best-effort enabled if present";
       - if not present, omits androidInfo from createInfo.next (the
         runtime will fall back to its own activity binding via the
         loader_init data we already passed in xrInitializeLoaderKHR).

Together these mean: if the create call still fails on PICO, you now know
*why* (XR_ERROR_API_VERSION_UNSUPPORTED, XR_ERROR_RUNTIME_UNAVAILABLE, etc.)
and can file a PICO-side ticket with a real error code instead of "-1".

Applies to: ReactVision/virocore @ master (and the equivalent file shipped
inside @reactvision/react-viro@2.55.0's libviro_renderer.so AAR).

How to consume this patch:

  $ git clone https://github.com/ReactVision/virocore.git
  $ cd virocore
  $ git checkout master
  $ git apply /Users/mikevocalz/expo-pico/patches/virocore/VROSceneRendererOpenXR.pico-compat.patch
  $ # Build sequence (see virocore/README.md):
  $ cd android
  $ ./gradlew :sharedCode:assembleRelease
  $ # Output: virocore/android/sharedCode/build/outputs/aar/sharedCode-release.aar
  $ # Replace the AAR inside the consumer's
  $ # node_modules/@reactvision/react-viro/android/viro_renderer/viro_renderer-release.aar
  $ # then run `expo prebuild --clean && bun run quest` to pick up the new .so.

Save this as a `bun patch @reactvision/react-viro` so it survives reinstalls.

---
 .../src/main/cpp/VROSceneRendererOpenXR.cpp   | 56 +++++++++++++++----
 1 file changed, 46 insertions(+), 10 deletions(-)

diff --git a/android/sharedCode/src/main/cpp/VROSceneRendererOpenXR.cpp b/android/sharedCode/src/main/cpp/VROSceneRendererOpenXR.cpp
--- a/android/sharedCode/src/main/cpp/VROSceneRendererOpenXR.cpp
+++ b/android/sharedCode/src/main/cpp/VROSceneRendererOpenXR.cpp
@@ -180,11 +180,21 @@ static const char *const kRequiredExtensions[] = {
-static const char *const kRequiredExtensions[] = {
-    XR_KHR_OPENGL_ES_ENABLE_EXTENSION_NAME,
-    XR_KHR_ANDROID_CREATE_INSTANCE_EXTENSION_NAME,
-};
-static constexpr uint32_t kRequiredExtensionCount =
-    sizeof(kRequiredExtensions) / sizeof(kRequiredExtensions[0]);
+// Hard requirements: every conformant OpenXR runtime exposes these. If one is
+// missing we genuinely cannot run.
+static const char *const kHardRequiredExtensions[] = {
+    XR_KHR_OPENGL_ES_ENABLE_EXTENSION_NAME,
+};
+static constexpr uint32_t kHardRequiredExtensionCount =
+    sizeof(kHardRequiredExtensions) / sizeof(kHardRequiredExtensions[0]);
+
+// Soft requirements: required on Quest, but PICO Swan rejects the create call
+// when these are enabled without the matching xrInitializeLoaderKHR prelude
+// having been done with the exact JavaVM / Activity refs the runtime expects.
+// We downgrade these to "enable iff enumerated".
+static const char *const kSoftRequiredExtensions[] = {
+    XR_KHR_ANDROID_CREATE_INSTANCE_EXTENSION_NAME,
+};
+static constexpr uint32_t kSoftRequiredExtensionCount =
+    sizeof(kSoftRequiredExtensions) / sizeof(kSoftRequiredExtensions[0]);

 static const char *const kOptionalExtensions[] = {
     XR_FB_PASSTHROUGH_EXTENSION_NAME,
@@ -245,9 +255,21 @@ bool VROSceneRendererOpenXR::initOpenXR() {
-    // Build the extension list: required + available optionals
-    std::vector<const char *> enabledExts(kRequiredExtensions,
-                                           kRequiredExtensions + kRequiredExtensionCount);
-    for (auto *optExt : kOptionalExtensions) {
+    // Build the extension list: hard-required + soft-required-if-present + optionals-if-present.
+    std::vector<const char *> enabledExts(kHardRequiredExtensions,
+                                           kHardRequiredExtensions + kHardRequiredExtensionCount);
+    bool androidCreateInstanceAvailable = false;
+    for (uint32_t i = 0; i < kSoftRequiredExtensionCount; ++i) {
+        auto *softExt = kSoftRequiredExtensions[i];
+        for (auto &ext : availableExts) {
+            if (strcmp(ext.extensionName, softExt) == 0) {
+                enabledExts.push_back(softExt);
+                if (strcmp(softExt, XR_KHR_ANDROID_CREATE_INSTANCE_EXTENSION_NAME) == 0)
+                    androidCreateInstanceAvailable = true;
+                break;
+            }
+        }
+    }
+    for (auto *optExt : kOptionalExtensions) {
         for (auto &ext : availableExts) {
             if (strcmp(ext.extensionName, optExt) == 0) {
                 enabledExts.push_back(optExt);
@@ -272,12 +294,26 @@ bool VROSceneRendererOpenXR::initOpenXR() {
     XrInstanceCreateInfo createInfo = { XR_TYPE_INSTANCE_CREATE_INFO };
-    createInfo.next                    = &androidInfo;
+    // Only chain XrInstanceCreateInfoAndroidKHR when the extension is enabled.
+    // PICO Swan rejects createInstance if the chain references an extension
+    // that wasn't in enabledExtensionNames.
+    createInfo.next                    = androidCreateInstanceAvailable ? (const void *)&androidInfo
+                                                                        : nullptr;
     createInfo.applicationInfo         = appInfo;
     createInfo.enabledExtensionCount   = (uint32_t)enabledExts.size();
     createInfo.enabledExtensionNames   = enabledExts.data();

-    XR_RETURN_FALSE(xrCreateInstance(&createInfo, &_instance));
+    XrResult createResult = xrCreateInstance(&createInfo, &_instance);
+    if (XR_FAILED(createResult)) {
+        char xrName[XR_MAX_RESULT_STRING_SIZE] = {0};
+        // xrResultToString needs an instance, which we don't have on failure.
+        // The numeric value is still actionable when cross-referenced against
+        // openxr.h's XrResult enum.
+        ALOGE("xrCreateInstance failed: XrResult=%d (androidCreateInstanceAvailable=%d, "
+              "enabledExtensions=%u)",
+              (int)createResult, (int)androidCreateInstanceAvailable,
+              createInfo.enabledExtensionCount);
+        return false;
+    }
     ALOGV("xrCreateInstance OK");

     return true;
